Here's how to implement this in .NET MAUI Shell:

## 1. Override `OnBackButtonPressed` and add a custom toolbar item

```csharp
public partial class EditProductPage : ContentPage
{
    private bool _hasUnsavedChanges;

    public EditProductPage()
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        Shell.SetBackButtonBehavior(this, new BackButtonBehavior
        {
            TextOverride = "Cancel",
            Command = new Command(async () => await ConfirmNavigation())
        });
    }

    protected override bool OnBackButtonPressed()
    {
        // Handle hardware/software back button (Android, etc.)
        if (_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            MainThread.BeginInvokeOnMainThread(async () => await ConfirmNavigation());
            return true; // Cancel default navigation
        }
        return base.OnBackButtonPressed();
    }

    private async Task ConfirmNavigation()
    {
        if (!_hasUnsavedChanges)
        {
            await Shell.Current.GoBack();
            return;
        }

        bool leave = await DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard and go back?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (leave)
            await Shell.Current.GoBack();
    }
}
```

## Key points

| Concern | Mechanism |
|---------|-----------|
| Custom back button text | `Shell.SetBackButtonBehavior` with `TextOverride` |
| Intercept shell back button tap | `BackButtonBehavior.Command` |
| Intercept hardware back (Android) | `OnBackButtonPressed()` returning `true` |
| Cancel navigation | Return `true` / don't call `GoBack()` |

## 2. Track unsaved changes

Flip `_hasUnsavedChanges = true` whenever a field changes (e.g., bind to `TextChanged` or use a dirty-tracking ViewModel):

```csharp
void OnFieldChanged(object sender, EventArgs e) => _hasUnsavedChanges = true;
```

## Caveats

- **iOS swipe-back gesture** — `BackButtonBehavior` disables the swipe gesture automatically when a `Command` is set.
- **Shell.GoBack()** is equivalent to pressing the system back button but won't re-trigger `OnBackButtonPressed`.
- If you use `Shell.SetBackButtonBehavior` in XAML instead:

```xml
<Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
    <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel" Command="{Binding GoBackCommand}" />
</Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
```

This covers hardware back, shell toolbar back, and gives you the "Cancel" label in one cohesive pattern.
